{
  "stem": "3341.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he came there, and because of his look, and his connections, he found what are the doctors.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he bribed one of them to give me in the evening-- because there was no penicillin, but there was a German substitute of penicillin-cibazol.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he bribed him, to give me in the night, two pills, or four pills.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Whatever was necessary in secret, because they wouldn't give it to the-- to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have to mention at this stage, then they brought in the first injured soldiers from the front, because the front was about 60 or 80 kilometers from the military hospital.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When they-- when the-- there were German injured soldiers, and also captured Polish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when the Polish soldiers, which were captured, when they were injured, they had to give-- they had to bring them to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the big military hospital.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they put two people in one bed, because there was such a shortage.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Luckily, they didn't put anyone to me, because they said, ah, maybe he will die anyhow.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I was not-- I was not bothered.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there I was, only until my brother started to arrange special treatment, because in the book, I found out after, every military patient has a diary, and they write so and so.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in my diary, on my name was written, very small chance of survival.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Patient will most probably not survive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the-- but thank God my brother had so much influence, that he put me through.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I was almost-- almost two months, when I was ready and commanded to go back to my unit, the unit, luckily, was replaced, not from the mountains, which we were before.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
